narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Daily practice is very helpful for learning Latin.

The second half of this class is more interesting than the first, but the textbook grammar is important to understanding Latin. If there could be a way to incorporate more of the "real Latin" into the first half, that could make it more interesting.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Latin is harder class compared to most Yale languages
Yes, a great class that will teach you not only how to read Latin, but also think about grammar more critically in general.
This course is probably a requirement for you, but it's a pretty good class. It's a lot of work, so just be sure to keep up.
